==Hawaiian==

===Etymology===
Proto East Polynesian: ''masalo''

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /mɒɦɒ'lɔʊ/

===Interjection===
'''mahalo'''
# [[thank you]]

====Usage notes====
#:*The word is widely employed on public notices in Hawaii, including on trash cans, leading some to mistakenly infer, going by context alone, the meaning of "[[trash]] [[can]]". 

